  <!-- 08 THE COPILOT -->
  <section id="copilot"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><div class="sec-num" data-pat="2,4,6"></div><div class="txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">08 — The product · Copilot</span>
      <h2 class="h2">How the Copilot actually talks to you.</h2>
      <p class="lead sec-sub">When you ask it something, it already has the whole farm in view. It answers in plain language and backs up what it says with the actual readings. Every answer ends on something you can do right then. Here's an exchange.</p>
    </div></div>
        <div class="shot narrow bare reveal"><img alt="AgriOS AI Copilot — chat sidebar with an explained irrigation recommendation, soil-moisture card, and suggested actions" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"></div>
    <div class="shot-cap reveal"><i data-lucide="sparkles"></i>The final screen · Copilot sidebar</div>
    <div class="annot reveal" style="margin-top:34px">
      <div class="a"><div class="h">It talks plainly</div><div class="r">The answer reads like a short briefing. <b>The point comes first</b>, the numbers after.</div></div>
      <div class="a"><div class="h">It shows its working</div><div class="r">Every claim is tied to a number you can check, like the <b>1.2&nbsp;mm forecast</b> or the 1.5% recovery.</div></div>
      <div class="a"><div class="h">It ends on something to do</div><div class="r">Each exchange finishes with <b>an action you can take</b>, and you can trace any answer back to the sensor logs.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
  </div>

  <!-- 09 DASHBOARD -->
  <section id="dashboard"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><div class="sec-num" data-pat="0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8"></div><div class="txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">09 — The product · Dashboard</span>
      <h2 class="h2">The dashboard is still here. It's just not in charge.</h2>
      <p class="lead sec-sub">I didn't get rid of the dashboard. It opens with the Copilot's read of the day instead of a wall of charts, and everything under that is there to back the read up. This is the overview screen for Divyesh's estate.</p>
    </div></div>

    <div class="shot reveal"><img alt="AgriOS dashboard Overview for Kadod Estate — AI Smart Farm Insight banner flagging two fields before the rain, alert cards for irrigation and disease, forecasted yield, and a field map" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"></div>
    <div class="shot-cap reveal"><i data-lucide="layers"></i>The final screen · the overview, Kadod Estate</div>
    <div class="annot reveal" style="margin-top:34px">
      <div class="a"><div class="h">The read comes first</div><div class="r">It opens by telling you what matters. <b>“Two fields need you before the rain at 16:00.”</b> The charts wait below.</div></div>
      <div class="a"><div class="h">Made for triage</div><div class="r">Two cards at the top, one for irrigation and one for disease, each with an action and a <b>“Why?”</b> beside it.</div></div>
      <div class="a"><div class="h">Charts as proof</div><div class="r">Yield, efficiency and the field map are <b>what the Copilot points at</b> when you question it. They aren't where you're made to start.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="dash-note">The charts didn't go anywhere. They just stopped being the first thing you have to figure out.</div>
  </div></section>

  <div class="band">
  <!-- 10 DECISIONS -->
  <section id="decisions"><div class="wrap-narrow">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><div class="sec-num" data-pat="1,4,7"></div><div class="txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">10 — The calls I made</span>
      <h2 class="h2">Most of the work went into trust.</h2>
      <p class="lead sec-sub">People don't hand things over to software they don't believe. So a lot of these calls weren't about making the Copilot smarter. They were about giving someone a reason to trust it. A few I went back and forth on.</p>
    </div></div>
    <div class="reveal" id="decisions-list"></div>
  </div></section>
