  <!-- 11 DESIGN SYSTEM -->
  <section id="system"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><div class="sec-num" data-pat="0,2,4,6,8"></div><div class="txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">11 — Design system</span>
      <h2 class="h2">A small system, built to keep advice calm.</h2>
      <p class="lead sec-sub">Nothing elaborate — just enough tokens, type and components to stay consistent. But one thing here mattered more than it looks. When a machine is the one giving the advice, the tone of the interface is doing trust work whether you intend it or not. An AgriOS that felt anxious — everything urgent, everything lit up — is one you’d quickly stop believing. So I rationed the alarm: green does the ordinary talking, and terracotta only ever means act now. And since the Copilot isn’t equally sure of everything, the system has to say so — a firm call and a rough estimate can’t look identical, or the interface is quietly lying about how far to trust it.</p>
    </div></div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-bottom:20px">
      <div class="ds-block reveal">
        <div class="h">Color tokens</div>
        <div class="swatches" id="swatches"></div>
