  <!-- 12 IMPACT -->
  <section id="impact"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head reveal"><div class="sec-num" data-pat="2,4,6"></div><div class="txt">
      <span class="eyebrow">12 — Projected impact</span>
      <h2 class="h2">What I think it would do, and how I'd check.</h2>
      <p class="lead sec-sub">Nothing shipped, so these aren't results. They're things I expect and would want to test. For each one I've tried to say why I think it'd happen, and the number I'd watch to see if it actually did.</p>
    </div></div>
    <div class="reveal" style="margin-bottom:26px"><div style="border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:3px solid var(--green);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;background:var(--surface)"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;letter-spacing:.13em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--green-2);margin-bottom:8px">The one number I’d watch</div><div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.6">If I could only move one thing, it’s <b>retention</b> — the daily active-decision rate. A subscription farm tool lives on whether people open it every day, and a dashboard doesn’t earn a daily open; a decision does. <b>Trust</b> is the gate in front of that, which is why the “Why?” and the stale-data honesty exist. Revenue I left alone — for a concept, that would just be a made-up figure.</div></div></div>
